<DocsLayout
  title="Rate Limit Time Windows - hitlimit | Sliding Window & Fixed Window"
  description="Configure rate limit time windows with human-readable strings like '1m', '1h', '1d'. Learn about sliding window vs fixed window algorithms. Millisecond precision support."
  keywords="rate limit window, sliding window rate limit, fixed window rate limit, time window configuration, rate limit duration, throttle window, api rate limit time, rate limiter algorithm"
>
  <h1>Time Windows</h1>
  <p>Configure rate limit time windows using human-readable strings or milliseconds.</p>

  <h2 id="string-format">String Format</h2>
  <div class="code-block">
    <pre><code><span class="str">'1s'</span>   <span class="cm">// 1 second</span>
<span class="str">'30s'</span>  <span class="cm">// 30 seconds</span>
<span class="str">'1m'</span>   <span class="cm">// 1 minute</span>
<span class="str">'15m'</span>  <span class="cm">// 15 minutes</span>
<span class="str">'1h'</span>   <span class="cm">// 1 hour</span>
<span class="str">'1d'</span>   <span class="cm">// 1 day</span></code></pre>
  </div>

  <h2 id="milliseconds">Milliseconds</h2>
  <div class="code-block">
    <pre><code><span class="fn">hitlimit</span>({"{"} limit: <span class="num">100</span>, window: <span class="num">60000</span> {"}"}) <span class="cm">// 1 minute in ms</span></code></pre>
  </div>

  <h2 id="sliding-window">Sliding Window</h2>
  <p>By default, hitlimit uses a sliding window algorithm for smoother rate limiting.</p>
</DocsLayout>

